vnto oure olde wyckednesse,
what other thynge do we, than pro|uoke
God vnto anger, mocke him, &amp;
seake the very destruccion of our co~+trey.
Lette vs therfore be the very
same in dede, that we haue promised
in worde. So shall it come to passe
assuredly, that God shall be in oure
army, fyght for vs, strengthen oure
